      <div class='col-xs-12 col-sm-10 col-sm-offlset-1 col-md-8 col-md-offset-2'>
<!-- timeline of his life -->
  <p id="ptext">Here's a brief timeline of his life:<p>
  <!-- Use li to do a single line, use <b> to bold small sections -->
        <li><b>1809</b> - Born in Shrewsbury, England</li>
        <li><b>1831</b> - Beings his voyage on the Beagle</li>
        <li><b>1835</b> - The Beagle arrives at Galapagos Island</li>
        <li><b>1836</b> - Charles returns home and begins publishing his theories</li>
  <li><b>1837</b> - He begins his first theories on species mutation</li>
  <li><b>1839</b> - Charles marries Emma Wedgewood</li>
  <li><b>1842</b> - Work begins on the descent of modification</li>
  <li><b>1856</b> - The theory of natural selection is developed</li>
  <li><b>1859</b> - On the origin of species by natural selection is published</li>
  <li><b>1864</b> - Charles recieves the Copley medal from the Royal Society of London</li>
  <li><b>1871</b> - Descent of Man, and Selection in Relation to Sex was published</li>
  <li><b>1882</b> - Charles Darwin died and was buried at Westminster Abbey</li>
      </div>
   </div>
